        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1903699239" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer251229852204438030"><b>“To all the scribes and artists and practitioners of magic through whom these spirits have been manifested….<br/>NOTHING IS TRUE. EVERYTHING IS PERMITTED.”</b><br/><br/>I’ve enjoyed Burroughs ‘s <i> Junky</i>, but this book was too bizarre for me. Even if we assume that there was any plot at all, I couldn’t follow it if I tried. The nonsensical dreamy sequence about naked men, sex and drugs eventually overwhelmed me and I had to put it down; that happened months ago and I’ve never picked it up again. So, I’m officially d</span>
  <span id="freeText251229852204438030" style="display:none"><b>“To all the scribes and artists and practitioners of magic through whom these spirits have been manifested….<br />NOTHING IS TRUE. EVERYTHING IS PERMITTED.”</b><br /><br />I’ve enjoyed Burroughs ‘s <i> Junky</i>, but this book was too bizarre for me. Even if we assume that there was any plot at all, I couldn’t follow it if I tried. The nonsensical dreamy sequence about naked men, sex and drugs eventually overwhelmed me and I had to put it down; that happened months ago and I’ve never picked it up again. So, I’m officially dnf-ing this because there are too many books out there that I would rather read instead.<br /></span>
